Hint: the large red areas around the hydroxyl group in 4-hydroxy-tamoxifen suggest that the molecule could benefit from hydrogen bond acceptors/negative atoms. Think of a small, electronegative atom which can accept a hydrogen bond. (Small because sterically demanding groups seem disfavorable in that area.) 

CoMFA contour maps in combination with estradiol-17β-glucuronide and 
cholic acid. Heteroatoms were rendered according to their default CPK colors.

(A) Steric field distribution. 
Regions where increasing the molecular volume increases activity are in
green and regions where increasing the volume decreases the activity are in 
yellow. 

(B) Electrostatic field distribution. 
Regions where increasing the positive charges increases activity
are in blue and regions where increasing the negative charges increases 
the activity are in red.
